# Row and sheet confirm actions (shared UI)

## Keyboard: Enter confirms, Escape cancels

App-wide convention (helpers in `core/keyboard-confirm-cancel.ts`):

- **`Enter`** — same as the green check / primary OK (`shouldKeyboardConfirmFromTarget`: not on `button` or `textarea`).
- **`Escape`** — same as the xmark cancel (`shouldKeyboardCancelFromTarget`). Always dismisses, including when a button is focused. App/budget pages also listen on `document:keydown.escape` so modals close reliably.

### Enter / Return confirms

- **Income & spending (`spendings-page`)**: `Enter` on an editing or new-entry row runs the same path as the green check (`onSpendingsTableRowEnterConfirm` → `confirmEditRow` / `confirmNewEntryRow`).
- **Accounts (`accounts-page`)**: `Enter` on new/edit row → `onAccountsTableRowEnterConfirm` → `confirmNewAccountRow` / `saveEdit`.
- **Budget table**: `Enter` in an in-table amount or one-off **position name** field confirms by blurring the field (`onBudgetTableFieldEnterConfirm`), matching “leave field to persist” behaviour.
- **Budget dialogs** (new position sheet, edit position modal): `Enter` on the `role="dialog"` root runs the primary action (`onBudgetSheetEnterConfirm`): blur the focused control first (so amount drafts flush), then `createPosition()` / `saveEditPosition()`.
- **App modals** (new/rename baseline, session expired): `Enter` on `role="dialog"` → `on*ModalEnterConfirm` in `app.ts`.

### Escape cancels

- **Spendings / accounts**: `Escape` on new or edit table rows → `on*TableRowEscapeCancel` → `tryClose*` / `tryCancel*` (confirm via `confirmDiscardUnsavedChanges` when the draft is dirty).
- **All cancel paths** (xmark, Escape, backdrop where applicable): use `tryClose*` / `tryCancel*` — never discard silently when the form is dirty.
- **Budget table**: `Escape` on one-off name reverts without save (`onBudgetPositionNameEscapeCancel`); on amount cell discards draft (`onBudgetCellAmountEscapeCancel`).
- **Budget sheets**: `Escape` on dialog → `onBudgetSheetEscapeCancel` → `closeNewPositionSheet` / `tryCloseEditPositionSheet` (category suggest still closes first via document listener).
- **App modals** (baseline, sharing, invitations, session): `Escape` on `role="dialog"` → `on*ModalEscapeCancel`; fallback `App.onDocumentEscapeCloseAppModal`. Sharing: `Enter` → create invite when owner. All dialogs: `tabindex="-1"`.
- **Budget sheets**: `tryCloseEditPositionSheet` / `tryCloseNewPositionSheet` (confirm when dirty); document listener delegates to these after category suggest.

## OK / Cancel affordances (match Einnahmen & Ausgaben)

For **inline table rows** and **budget bottom sheets / modals** where the user confirms or discards a row or form:

- **Confirm**: **`app-table-icon-btn app-table-icon-btn--confirm`**, **`fa-sharp fa-solid fa-check`**, `aria-label` and `title` from **`budget.confirmEntry`** (German “Übernehmen”, English “Confirm”).
- **Cancel**: **`app-table-icon-btn app-table-icon-btn--cancel`**, **`fa-sharp fa-solid fa-xmark`**, `aria-label` and `title` from **`app.cancel`**.
- Wrap the pair in `inline-flex items-center justify-end gap-1` (see `spendings-page.component.html` action cells and `budget-page.component.html` sheet footers).

Do **not** use the older wide violet “Save” + text “Cancel” footer for new flows unless there is a strong reason; keep parity with `spendings-page` for confirm/discard.

## View-mode row actions (edit / delete)

For read-only table rows (accounts, spendings, budget positions):

- Wrap actions in **`app-table-row-actions`** (`inline-flex`, end-aligned, `gap-1`).
- **Edit**: **`app-table-icon-btn app-table-icon-btn--edit`**, icon **`fa-sharp fa-solid fa-pen-to-square`**, `aria-label`/`title` from **`budget.barEdit`** (budget rows may use **`budget.editRowHint`** for `title` when opening the position dialog).
- **Delete**: **`app-table-icon-btn app-table-icon-btn--delete`**, icon **`fa-sharp fa-solid fa-trash-can`**, `aria-label`/`title` from **`budget.delete`**.
- Icon-only buttons (no text labels); shared styles live in `styles.css`.

## Delete affordance (avoid Cancel/Delete confusion)

For row-level destructive actions in tables (e.g. accounts, spendings, budget):

- Use a dedicated trash icon: **`fa-sharp fa-solid fa-trash-can`** (never `fa-xmark` for delete).
- Do **not** use `fa-xmark` for delete; `xmark` is reserved for **Cancel** (`app.cancel`).

